 for modeling complex dynamics in the physical world.

Two PhD positions are available at Sorbonne University on the following 
topic: Deep Learning for modeling complex dynamics in the physical world.

Both positions focus on the challenge of combining prior physical 
knowledge together with machine learning for modeling complex 
spatio-temporal dynamics.

-    One position is available at Sorbonne-University, Abou Dhabi, on 
the Modeling of Dynamical Systems  with Geoscience Application: 
https://mlia.lip6.fr/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/PhD-position_SUAD-Deep-Learning-for-Modeling-Physical-Dynamics.pdf

-    One position is available at Sorbonne University, Paris, on Deep 
Learning in Computational Fluid Dynamics : 
